<br>
No, we dont need to spend any more time in the spellbook.  You missunderstand what it means to be a raid healer.  If you go into your book for anything but a healing spell you are being inefficiant.  The only arguement i have ever seen with wieght is that clerics should help when the call for nuke comes in on gating mobs.... because at that point DPS is more important than anything else.<br>
<br>
when im on a raid, my spell loadout is remedy/celestial healing/complete heal/divine light/Words of vigor/divine aura/divine barrier/ and one open slot.  that slot is useually either stun when the mobs can be stunned to help with agro management (I stun mobs off the chanter), or so form of offinsive spell to help with DPS. (mark of retribution, or a nuke)<br>
<br>
note that the 8th spell is never cast when I have less than 30 mana at the end of a fight. I will gage the power of the healing being done, and &quot;play&quot; with my one spell as i can, IE some nights not at all cause I need to watch too many people's heath (normaly I am assigned my own group and two melees outside it)<br>
<br>
So agian i say... if you want to be number 2 healer, start by respecializing Alter, meming a veriety of healing spells, and keeping up some situationals to help with the raid. But NEVER EVER SAY A CLERIC HAS TIME TO MESS AROUND WITH THE REST OF THEIR SPELLS DURING A RAID. <p>____________________________________________
