<br>
On any given day, here are all the spells I will ever use: (in order) Complete Heal, Divine Light, Celestial Elixir, Remedy, Aegolism (for others, I get POTG for myself), Marzin, Divine Intervention, Divine Aura, Divine Barrier, possible I'll cast mok/mor if the mob isnt 100% MR.<br>
<br>
As for &quot;utility&quot; spells, I can summon a no drop hammer, summon something to eat or drink, summon a magic headband, gate myself, discover true north and make myself invisble to the undead.<br>
<br>
Of all of those, Bind and Gate are the only ones that get used really.<br>
<br>
No cleric in a group is going to use their precious eight spell slots to drop all their heals/divines/buffs for &quot;utility&quot; spells.<br>
<br>
All Clerics do is heal people. Everything else is secondary. Every cleric in the game could have the best res, and it would not makes monsters die any faster. I wouldn't think that &quot;oh, I should invite a Necromancer in case we die, he can summon us!&quot; I don't think people think like that.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I don't support the petition, but I do hope some of the issues get fixed like single target POTG, epic, etc... Good luck. <p>Alliliel Archfalcon<br>
